      <entry xml:id="entry_lakʼami" xml:lang="os-x-iron">
        <form type="lemma"><orth>lakʼami</orth><form type="variant"><orth>likʼami</orth></form><form
            type="variant"><orth>likʼani</orth></form></form>
        <usg><lang/></usg>
        <sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
            <q>постный пирог с солодом, круглой или ромбовидной формы</q>
          </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
            <q>vegetable pie with malt, round or diamond-shaped</q>
          </abv:tr>; <note xml:lang="ru" type="comment">изготовляется в первый день жатвы, а также
            для посвящений покойнику</note><note xml:lang="en" type="comment">made on the first day
            of harvest, and also as a dedication to a deceased person</note></sense>
        <abv:exampleGrp>
          <abv:example>
            <quote>dæ ʒyx lakʼamijy jas</quote>
            <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
              <q>рот у тебя величиной с <hi rendition="#rend_smallcaps">lakʼami</hi></q>
            </abv:tr>
            <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
              <q>your mouth is the size of a <hi rendition="#rend_smallcaps"
                  ><oRef>lakʼami</oRef></hi></q>
            </abv:tr>
            <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Брит."/><biblScope>161</biblScope></bibl>
          </abv:example>
        </abv:exampleGrp>
        <etym xml:lang="ru">Ср. <mentioned xml:lang="ka"><lang/><w>likʼani</w><gloss><q>вид
                хлеба</q></gloss>(<note type="comment"><cit>
                <q rendition="#rend_doublequotes">torneši čaqudebuli pʼuri</q>
                <bibl>: <ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Саба"/></bibl>
              </cit></note>)</mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sva"
                ><lang/><w>lukʼvan</w><gloss><q>пирог с начинкой</q></gloss></mentioned>.
          Первоисточник, вероятно, — <mentioned xml:lang="ar"><lang/><w>luqma</w><gloss><q>сладкая
                круглая оладья</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ar"
                ><w>luqum</w><gloss><q>вид сладкого блина</q></gloss></mentioned>.</etym>
        <etym xml:lang="en">Cf. <mentioned xml:lang="ka"><lang/><w>likʼani</w><gloss><q>a kind of
                bread</q></gloss>(<note type="comment"><cit>
                <q rendition="#rend_doublequotes">torneši čaqudebuli pʼuri</q>
                <bibl>: <ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Саба"/></bibl>
              </cit></note>)</mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sva"
                ><lang/><w>lukʼvan</w><gloss><q>stuffed pie</q></gloss></mentioned>. The original
          source is probably <mentioned xml:lang="ar"><lang/><w>luqma</w><gloss><q>sweet round
                cake</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ar"><w>luqum</w><gloss><q>a kind
                of sweet pancake</q></gloss></mentioned>.</etym>
